Emotional Intellegence

Lack of EQ can hold you back in your career

Strengths: Empathy, Conflict Management
Weaknesses: Coach / Mentor

EI: Mkaing your emotions work for you.
  Being in touch with your emotions and being able to channel them to benefit yourself and others

  Moods: less intense feeloings with nos pecific trigger, long term
  Attitudes: general approach or perception of a situation
  Emotions: intense feelings caused by a specific event for a short-term: what are some things that impact?

What can impact our emotions:
  -Personality
  -Stress
  -Social Activities / Relationships
  -Sleep
  -Exercise
  -Age
  -Gender

PICTURE ON TAKEAWAYS OF OPRAHS AMD DANIEL GOLEMANS VIDEO

Difference between IQ and EQ?
  -IQ is NOT what matters most; tells what you can do but not how you do it
  -Keys: Self-Awareness of what you're feeling, why you're feeling it - can't manage yourself effectively without
    -Empathy: Aligning ourslef with others, feel what they feel
    -Flow: PICTURE

Percieve Emotions in Self
  -Become aware of percerptions, biases, expectations
  -Hone senses
  -Link outward manifestations to feeling

Percieve Emotions in Others
  -Direct Observations
  -Assumptions
  -Inference
  -Interpretation
  -Feeling
  -Aha! Moments

Techniques to Develop EI
  -Reflection
  -Relaxation
  -Mindfulness
  -Cognitive Control / Reframe
  -Emotional Control
  -Develop values system
  -Balance skill level with challenge
  -Reflect back emotional intent

Nov8---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Tourism: Movement of people to somewhere they dont usually go

Hospitality: The combination of accomodation/lodging and food/beverage

Tourism is one of the largest industries in the world.
  Positives:
    -1-7 people are engaging in tourism in any given year.
    -10% of worldwide GDP
    -1.5 trillion of that is in international tourism
    -Counts as balance of trade & an export
    -Tourism provides countless jobs for everyone, including the less educated
    -Local products sold at tourism hotspots further help the local economy (Ex: Carribean)

  Negatives:
    -Environmental Damage
      -People dont treat the environment with as much respect on vacations as they do at home.
    -Property Values Increase
      -They increase to the point where locals cannot afford to live there anymore.
    -Changes the home-nations culture
      -So much tourism can change how locals can "lose their identity"
    -During the bad tourism season, entire towns shut down and become ghost towns
    -Natural Disasters can destory an area's economy
      -Jersey Shores tourism died after hurricane, so people didnt go there because the beaches werent nice

Dont worry about convention and rec and entertainment

Hotel Market Segments:
  -Commercial Segment
    -Caters to a business traveler
    -Makes a majority of their money Mon-Thurs
    -Co-locate to where business' are in the area
  -Leisure Segment
    -The one where the tourists want to go with ammendities.
    -Beaches, Theme parks, Jet Skis
    -The idea is that you go on a vacation to have lots of fun
  -Meetings and Groups
    -Giant hotels with lots of rooms with HUGE ballrooms
    -They have to have lots of space for common dining
    -Include Conference Hotels
    -Never have to leave the building. Full Service hotel
  -Extended Stay
    -Places like residence inn's
    -Maybe moving a family and might be in temporary housing for a while
    -Has a kitchen, living room. Will feel more like an apartment than a hotel.
    -They know you will be in this situation for weeks/months.
KEEP IN MIND THERE IS CROSSOVER IN ALL OF THESE
  -Will have to find the PRIMARY Market Segment

Major Types of Resurants
  -QSR, Quick Service Resurant
    -Same thing as Fast Food
    -Ex: McDonalds, Wendys, Burger King, etc.
    -Its okay food, typically dont tip, relatively low price
  -Fast Casual
    -Little more upscale in environment and food quiality than QSR
    -Ex: Panera, Chipotle
    -Dont put emphasis on efficiency
    
  -Full Service
    -Family Resurants
      -Ex: Golden Corall, Chuck-E-Cheese
      -Really noisy, alot of families go there.
      -Food quality is okay.
    -Casual
      -A little more upscale than Family Resturant in environment and food quility
      -A little more expensive
        -Ex: Red Robin, Olive Garden
    -Ethnic
      -Anytime the resturant is completely based on nations food
    -Fine Dining
      -Really expensive and really nice food
      -Nice silverware
      -No emphasis on speed of service.
      -Ex: Capital Grill, Ruths Chris, Mortons
      -A special occasion thing.

Institutional Food Service
  -Food being sold in bulk, and being prepared in a huge kitchen
  -Not a whole lot of variety
  -Ex: Airports, Prisons, Hospitals

Dont need to know profitability of resturant types

