Accounting: All the actiity that goes into accurately stating the finanical standing of a business
  -The process of measuring and summarizing business activities, interpreting finincial information,
  and communicating the results to management and other decision makers.
  
FASB Financial Accounting Standards Board, sets the GAAP
 -GAAP (Generally Accepted Accounting Principals)

Financial Statements
  -Balance Sheet
    A snapshot at any given point in time of the company's assets and liabilities
    
    
    
  -Income Statement
    Shows you how much we made in revenue and how much we spent in costs, and shows profit

Fudamental Accounting Equation
  Assets - Liabilities = Owners Equity
(What you own) - (What you owe) = (Net worth)
    OR
Assets = Liabilities + Owners Equity

Revenue - Expenses = Profit

Liquidity: The speed at which you can transfer an item into cash
  Cash: Highest Liquidity
  Property: Lowest Liquidity

PUT BALANCE SHEET IN ORDER OF LIQUIDITY
  IF YOU PUT IT IN THE SAME ORDER AS GIVEN, ITS GOOD

Question: Why is Other Current more Liquid than Securities

Accoutning uses T accounts

Every account has a credit and debit side

Things you OWN go on debit side
Things you OWE go on credit side

Must always balance credits and debits in accounting

Debit Side: Assets and Expenses
Credit Side: Revenue and Liabilities/Owners Equity

Difference between Accountant and Financial Manager
  Accountant: Taxes, prepares financial statement, scorkeeper
  Financial Manager: Raising capital for the firm, investing money for the firm / for clients
    Decide whats going on in the financial statement and investing accoringly
      TAKES ACTION ON ACCOUNTANTS RECORDS

Two different types of accoutnign
  Financial Accounting: Preparing financial statements for the outside world
  Managerial accounting: Directed more towards the inside of the company.

Financial Ratios: 
Category's
  -Profitability Ratios 
    Take the profit and divide it by something
      Ex: Profit / #Shares = EPS: Earnings per share *REMEMBER THIS ONE, IT GUIDES STOCK MARKET*
  -Liquidity Ratios
    Tell you how ready is the company to pay its near term obligation
  -Debt Ratios
    How much of the financial structure of the company is already borrowed

Break-Even Analysis:
  Types of costs: Fixed(Salaries, Building rental) and Variable Costs (Labor, Raw Materials)

Selling price: 1.25, Manufacturing costs: .75, fixed costs 1.5m per year

How many units to break-even? 1.5m / .50 = 3 million units

ON THE FINAL: Word problem that mixed mark-up with breakeven

Conveneice sells at 4
Markup 25%
THEY PAY 3.2

MARGIN: 1.7
Cost 1.50
foed 340,000

340,000 / 1.7 = *200,000*

They sell at  1000
