Personal Finance:

Credit Score: FICO Score (The organization that make the idea of credit score)

Ways to improve credit score: 
  -Pay it on time, being late highly affects your score
  -Pay off your credit card completely card every month
  -Cosign and Loans with other people
    -Its not a good idea because oyu dont want to subject yourself because of their behavior
  -Keep your spending managable
  -Postpone purchase of indulgence items

Financial Planning (Three Steps)
  -Building Wealth
    -Trying to build up wealth so you dont have to live off of Social Security
  -Presering the Wealth
  -Living off of what your preserved

Time Value of Money: Take the money now and not in five years
  -Opprotunity cost of not investing rn
  -Inflation devalues the money in 5 years

Simple Interest: Interest made on only the original investment
Compound Interest: Interrest on Interest

simple: principle * interest rate

FINAL: THERE WILL BE A QUESTION ON SIMPLE OR COMPOUND INTEREST 

Diversification: Dont but all your eggs in one basket
  -You want to invest in various different classes
    -Stocks, Mutual Funds (ETF), CD's, Bonds, Commodities

Recommendations on when debt is good:
  -First house
  -Student loans, worthwhile investment

  -DONT BUY cars, they depreciate very fast
  -Dont revolve credit on a credit card

Secured vs Unsecured Credit
  -Collateral: The thing the lender can take back if you dont pay.

Secured has collateral, unsecured does not

